Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Speedy Sriracha Chicken Udon Noodles in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Stir-Fried Veg ==

Trim and halve the @green beans{80%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken thigh{240%g} and beans to the pan and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the chicken is cooked, add the garlic and @coleslaw mix{120%g}. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

== Noodles ==

Add the @udon noodles{220%g} to the pan. Toss to coat, using a #fork{} to gently separate them.

Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Sauce ==

Add the @ketjap manis{50%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml} and @honey{15%g} to the noodles.

Toss together so everything's evenly coated in the sauce.

Stir-fry until piping hot, ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{splash} if you feel it needs it.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Share the noodles between your #serving bowls{} and drizzle over the @hot sauce{30%g}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder) to finish.

Enjoy!